{
  "texts": [
    "For simplicity, we assume the numerical errors of these three components are also bounded by ε respectively.",
    "Let (3.22) s(x, t) = -sK (x, t) + 1 2 Σ(x, t)sB(x, t) -sL(x, t).Subtracting equation (3.20) by (3.21) we have(3.23) X * t+∆t (x) -X N t+∆t (x) = X * t (x) -X N t (x) + d 2 X * t (x) 2 dt 2 t=τ (∆t) 2 + ∇b(X t,ξ, t) • (X * t (x) -X N t (x))∆t - 1 2 ∇Σ(X t,ξ ′) • (X * t (x) -X N t (x))∆t + eK ∆t - 1 2 eB∆t + eL∆t,where e K, e B and e L are given in the following.",
    "First, based on the law of large numbers and the assumption that the kernel function is twice-differentiable, for the bounded interaction (1),Ex|eK |:= Ex Ω K(X * t (x) -y) pt(y) dy -sK (X N t (x), t) ≤ Ex Ω K(X * t (x) -y) pt(y) dy - Ω K(X N t (x) -y) pt(y) dy + Ex Ω K(X N t (x) -y) pt(y) dy -sK (X N t (x), t) ≤ C1Ex X * t (x) -X N t (x) + ε,This manuscript is for review purposes only.whereC 1 = 2 sup x∈Ω |∇ • K(x)| < ∞.",
    "For the Biot-Savart interaction (2), Ex |eK | ≤ Ex Ω K(X * t (x) -y) pt(y) dy - Ω K(X N t (x) -y) pt(y) dy + Ex Ω K(X N t (x) -y) pt(y) dy -sK (X N t (x), t) = Ex Ω K(z) pt(z + X * t (x)) dz - Ω K(z) pt(z + X N t (x)) dz + Ex Ω K(X N t (x) -y) pt(y) dy -sK (X N t (x), t) = Ex Ω -U (z) • ∇ pt(z + X * t (x)) dz + Ω U (z) • ∇ pt(z + X N t (x)) dz + Ex Ω K(X N t (x) -y) pt(y) dy -sK (X N t (x), t) ≤ C2Ex X * t (x) -X N t (x) + ε,whereC 2:= sup t∈[t0,T] ∇ x Ω U (z) • ∇ p t (z + x) dz ∞ < ∞.",
    "Second, |eB|:= Σ(X * t (x), t)∇ log pt(X * t (x)) -Σ(X N t (x), t)sB(X N t (x), t) ≤ Σ(X * t (x), t)∇ log pt(X * t (x)) -Σ(X * t (x), t)∇ log pt(X N t (x)) + Σ(X * t (x), t)∇ log pt(X N t (x)) -Σ(X N t (x), t)∇ log pt(X N t (x)) + Σ(X N t (x), t)∇ log pt(X N t (x)) -Σ(X N t (x), t)sB(X N t (x), t) ≤ C3|X * t -X N t | + ε,whereC 3 = sup t∈[t0,T] sup x∈Ω C σ ∇ 2 log p t (x) + ∥∇ log p t ∥ ∞ |∇ • Σ(x, t)| < ∞."
